RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 87. Claiming Purse 8500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MAY 6, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPIRE was allowed to settle while racing two-wide, rallied four-wide into the stretch and finished fast to be up in the final strides. IRON ROB saved ground stalking the pace, angled out to be three-wide at the quarter pole, took the lead leaving the eighth pole and then just failed to last in a game effort. NATIONHEART saved ground setting the pace, responded when headed and held on fairly well during the drive for third. MANAALABOUTDAMONEY prompted the pace from along the outside into the stretch and weakened. RIVER ROSE stumbled at the start, then saved ground while being reserved off the pace but failed to threaten. SMOKE AND BURN was unhurried early, came five-wide into the stretch and was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: River Rose
ENTRY.COMMENT: stumbled start, reserved, saved ground, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Nationheart
ENTRY.OWNER: James Carter R and Soranno Jillian
